FBIS3-13764 "drnes054_d_94006" FBIS-NES-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 17 Mar 1994 Libya Suspects in 1993 Coup Attempt Reportedly Tortured NC1703184694 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 17 Mar 94 NC1703184694 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] A Libyan opposition group has announced that the Libyan (?intelligence service) tortured Libyan Army officers who had been involved in an unsuccessful bid to overthrow the regime and forced them to appear on television to publicly confess that they had been spying for the United States. A spokesman for the Libyan National Salvation Front [words indistinct] that Libyan leader Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi continued to deny there had been a rebellion even though Arab diplomatic sources in Libya assert that a rebellion really did occur. At the time of the rebellion, press sources said it was organized by Islamic hardliners among the Army officers. These sources said the rebellion started on 11 October 1993.
